  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Exception Summary 
    Class Description
    Activity
    Abstract superclass for Course and Event classes
    ArrayList<E>
    The purpose of the ArrayList class is to keep track of a list of generic objects and be able to manipulate and utilize the list with ease.
    ArrayQueue<E>
    The purpose of the customized ArrayQueue is to keep track of a queue of generic objects and be able to utilize the functionality of a queue with ease.
    ArrayStack<E>
    The purpose of the customized ArrayStack is to keep track of a stack of generic objects and be able to utilize the functionality of a stack with ease.
    Conflict
    Interface that will check to see if two Activities are conflicting with one another
    ConflictException
    Specialized exception to be thrown when two Activity objects are conflicting
    Course
    Course class represents a course offered by the university and contains information about said course.
    CourseCatalog
    The purpose of the CourseCatalog object is to create and keep track of a list of Courses that are available at the university.
    CourseCatalogPanel
    Creates a user interface for working with the CourseCatalog.
    CourseNameValidator
    The purpose of the CourseNameValidator class is to determine if a course name is valid for application to the PackSchedular Program as whole.
    CourseNameValidatorFSM
    Finite State Machine for checking whether a Course's Name is valid.
    CourseRecordIO
    Reads Course records from text files.
    CourseRoll
    The CourseRoll class establishes an enrollment capacity for its associated Course and stores the Students enrolled in the Course along with the waitlist for the Course.
    Faculty
    The purpose of the Faculty class is to provide a place to store information for an individual Faculty.
    FacultyDirectory
    The purpose of the FacultyDirectory class is to maintain a directory of all Faculty enrolled at NC State.
    FacultyDirectoryPanel
    Creates a user interface for working with the FacultyDirectory.
    FacultyRecordIO
    Deals with reading and writing of files with information on Faculty users.
    FacultySchedule
    A Faculty's schedule
    FacultySchedulePanel
    Creates a user interface for a Faculty to view the Courses that they are teaching and which Students are enrolled in the Course along with other Course details.
    InstructorAssignmentPanel
    Creates a user interface for a registrar to assign/remove faculty to/from courses.
    InvalidTransitionException
    The purpose of the InvalidTransitionException class is to inform the client that they have made an invalid transition between states.
    LinkedAbstractList<E>
    The purpose of the LinkedAbstractList class is to keep track of multiple items in a list and manipulate that list through the use of the methods that are implemented.
    LinkedList<E>
    The custom LinkedList class extends the functionality of AbstractSequentialList and doesn’t allow for null elements or duplicate elements as defined by the equals() method.
    LinkedListRecursive<E>
    The LinkedListRecursive class maintains the same functionality as the custom LinkedList but utilizes recursive private methods inside of the private inner ListNode class to accomplish that functionality.
    LinkedQueue<E>
    The purpose of the customized LinkedQueue is to keep track of a Queue of generic objects and be able to utilize the functionality of a Queue with ease.
    LinkedStack<E>
    The purpose of the customized LinkedStack is to keep track of a stack of generic objects and be able to utilize the functionality of a stack with ease.
    PackSchedulerGUI
    Main GUI for the PackScheduler project.
    Queue<E>
    An interface to implement the FIFO functionality of a Queue.
    RegistrationManager
    RegistrationManager handles registration for Students and Faculty into their respective directories.
    Schedule
    Maintains the Schedule object for PackScheduler.
    Stack<E>
    An interface to implement the LIFO functionality of a Stack.
    Student
    The purpose of the Student class is to provide a place to store information for an individual student.
    StudentDirectory
    The purpose of the StudentDirectory class is to maintain a directory of all students enrolled at NC State.
    StudentDirectoryPanel
    Creates a user interface for working with the StudentDirectory.
    StudentRecordIO
    The purpose of the StudentRecordIO class is to have specific functionality in order to read and write information from files.
    StudentRegistrationPanel
    Creates a user interface for students to register for classes.
    User
    methods for the abstract class User
